\ ask-claude.l4 — ask Claude a question via the Anthropic Messages API.
\ exercises: env (read the API key from the environment), frame>json (build
\ the JSON request body), subprocesses (curl via start-process / read-out),
\ json>frame (parse the reply), frame + array access.
\
\ Needs ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in the environment and curl on the PATH.

"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001" to MODEL

\ Build the Messages-API request body from a question string.
: request-body ( question -- json )
  |> question |
  { :model MODEL  :max_tokens 256
    :messages [ { :role "user" :content question } ] }
  frame>json ;

\ POST the body to the API with curl, return the parsed response frame.
\ start-process (not run) because the header and body args contain spaces.
: call-api ( body -- response )
  |> body |
  [ "curl" "-s" "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
    "-H" "x-api-key: " "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY" env +
    "-H" "anthropic-version: 2023-06-01"
    "-H" "content-type: application/json"
    "-d" body ] start-process read-out
  json>frame ;

\ Ask Claude, returning its answer text (or the raw error JSON on failure).
: ask ( question -- answer )
  request-body call-api
  dup :content has? if
    :content @  0 @i  :text @
  else
    frame>json
  then ;

"In one sentence, what is a stack-based programming language?" ask . cr
bye
